result.execSummary:
The defendant George Edward Eickhoff was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess/Illegally Obtained Prescription [Modifiers: Penalty-Fraud/Obtaining Prescriptions], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 450.11(7)(h).
  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

10:33 AM Defendant George Edward Eickhoff in court.  Attorney Mark David Lawton in court for George Edward Eickhoff.  Prosecuting attorney Brenda L. Yaskal in court for the State of Wisconsin. Agreement recited by State. Court reviewed the rights & elements. Defendant pled no contest to counts 5 & 6. Court found defendant guilty, entered judgment. Sentencing statements. Court withheld sentence, placed the defendant on probation for 2 years. Conditions of probation include: Not possess or consume controlled substances without a valid Rx. Not possess drug paraphernalia. No possession or consumption of alcoholic beverages. Can not be charged with any crime or ordinance that contorts with a crime. Complete an AODA assessment and follow through with any treatment recommendations. Submit DNA sample. Costs on count 5 of $443.00 and costs of $243.00 on count 6. Defendant may request expungement of this case upon successful completion of probation and all conditions. 3 days jail credit. 10:47 AM
